itemLabel: John Edward Deane Browne, 5th Baron Kilmaine

wikipedia_page.main: John Edward Deane Browne, 5th Baron Kilmaine  (18 March 1878 – 27 August 1946) was an Anglo-Irish politician and landowner. He sat in the House of Lords, within the Imperial British Parliament, as an Irish representative peer (1911–1946).
